          XPointer arg;

  AARRGGUUMMEENNTTSS

    arg
        Specifies the user-supplied argument that will be passed to the
        predicate procedure.

    display
        Specifies the connection to the X server.

    event_return
        Returns either a copy of or the matched event's associated structure.

    predicate
        Specifies the procedure that is to be called to determine if the next
        event in the queue matches what you want.

  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The XXIIffEEvveenntt function completes only when the specified predicate
    procedure returns True for an event, which indicates an event in the queue
    matches. XXIIffEEvveenntt flushes the output buffer if it blocks waiting for
    additional events. XXIIffEEvveenntt removes the matching event from the queue and
    copies the structure into the client-supplied XXEEvveenntt structure.

    When the predicate procedure finds a match, XXCChheecckkIIffEEvveenntt copies the
    matched event into the client-supplied XXEEvveenntt structure and returns True.
    (This event is removed from the queue.) If the predicate procedure finds
    no match, XXCChheecckkIIffEEvveenntt returns False, and the output buffer will have
    been flushed. All earlier events stored in the queue are not discarded.

    The XXPPeeeekkIIffEEvveenntt function returns only when the specified predicate
    procedure returns True for an event. After the predicate procedure finds a
    match, XXPPeeeekkIIffEEvveenntt copies the matched event into the client-supplied
    XXEEvveenntt structure without removing the event from the queue. XXPPeeeekkIIffEEvveenntt
    flushes the output buffer if it blocks waiting for additional events.

